<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cubs Put Hill on Disabled List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- The Chicago Cubs placed outfielder Glenallen  
Hill on the 15-day disabled list Sunday with a strained right 
hamstring and called up Bo Porter from Triple-A Iowa. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill became the ninth Cub to go on the disabled list this  
season. Pitchers Kevin Tapani, Terry Adams and Jon Lieber recently 
came off the disabled list, and Matt Karchner, Jeremi Gonzalez, 
Kurt Miller, Robin Jennings and Kerry Wood remain on it. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill hit .452 with five homers and 15 RBIs in 15 games before  
aggravating the hamstring last week. 
</P>
<P>
	Porter got his first call-up to the major leagues after hitting  
.280 with five homers in 25 games for Iowa. 
</P>
<P>
	Tapani, who had been disabled by tightness in his shoulder, made  
his second start since coming off the disabled list on Friday and 
was hit on the left wrist by Eddie Taubensee's line drive. 
</P>
<P>
	Tapani remained in the game, but X-rays on Saturday found he had  
broken the hamate bone by the outside of the wrist. Since it's his 
glove hand, he'll be able to keep pitching while the bone heals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
