<HEADLINE> Gordon May Be Activated by Red Sox </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Boston Red Sox closer Tom Gordon, on the disabled  
list since April 18 because of a strained right elbow, might be 
ready to return. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're taking it day by day, but he could possibly be back  
tomorrow,'' Red Sox manager Jimy Williams said after Sunday's 6-1 
win over Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
	Infielder Donnie Sadler was optioned to Pawtucket after Sunday's  
game, a move that seemed to indicate that the Red Sox were prepared 
to activate Gordon. 
</P>
<P>
	Gordon was trying to extend his major league record of 46  
straight saves on April 17 against the Tampa Bay Devil Rays when he 
left the game after throwing five pitches. 
</P>
<P>
	``I feel good. I think I need to face some hitters and get back  
in the game,'' Gordon said. ``Right now, I'm a little lacking in 
arm strength, but that comes with pitching. I'm ready to go.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Red Sox bullpen has struggled in Gordon's absence, blowing  
seven save chances this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams gave Tim Wakefield a shot on Thursday night and he  
responded, saving a 3-2 victory over Texas. Wakefield got his 
second save Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I did it more for the club's sake,'' he said. ``Whatever it  
takes to help the team win. It turned out I was needed out there.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
