<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Marquez To Defend NABO Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Juan Manuel Marquez of Mexico defends  
his NABO featherweight championship tomorrow night against Wilfredo 
Vargas of Puerto Rico at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
	The 12-round bout will be the eighth defense for Marquez, who  
won the title on Feb. 3, 1997 by stopping Cedric Mingo of Anaheim, 
Calif., in the 10th round. 
</P>
<P>
	Marquez, 25, is 28-1 with 22 knockouts. He hasn't lost since  
being beaten by Javier Duran of Mexico City in his professional 
debut nearly six years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Marquez hopes to fight WBO featherweight champion Naseem Hamed  
at some point in the near future. 
</P>
<P>
	Vargas, 28, is 23-11 with 18 knockouts and has three failed  
attempts at winning WBO championships. 
</P>
<P>
	Rafael Marquez, Juan Manuel's younger brother, will also fight  
on Monday night's card, facing Angel Almena of Puerto Rico in a 
10-round bantamweight bout. 
</P>
<P>
	The younger Marquez, 24, has a 16-1 record with 14 knockouts  
while Almena, 25, is 14-3 with nine knockouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
