<HEADLINE> Rangers Activate Burkett Off DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Right-hander John Burkett was activated  
by the Texas Rangers and was scheduled to start tonight against the 
Toronto Blue Jays. 
</P>
<P>
	Left-handed reliever Eric Gunderson was put on the 15-day  
disabled list, retroactive to Saturday, because of tightness in his 
left shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Burkett went onto the DL on April 21 because of bursitis in his  
right shoulder. In two rehab assignments with Double-A Tulsa, 
Burkett was 0-1 with a 2.70 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	Burkett is 0-2 with a 12.00 ERA in three starts this season with  
the Rangers. His last outing was a 4-0 loss against the Yankees on 
April 20. 
</P>
<P>
	Gunderson is 0-0 with a 7.20 ERA in 11 relief appearances.  
</P>
</TEXT>
