<DOCNO> APW19990509.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-09 20:16:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Crew 2, Clash 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Jeff Cunningham scored twice to give the  
Columbus Crew a 2-1 win over the San Jose Clash on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The win put the Crew (5-2) in first place in the Eastern  
Conference, moving one point ahead of D.C. United. 
</P>
<P>
	Cunningham, making his second start of the season, opened  
scoring in the 17th minute of play. Clash goalkeeper Joe Cannon 
stopped a shot by Billy Thompson, but Crew defender Thomas Dooley 
got the rebound and sent a pass to Cunningham for the goal. 
</P>
<P>
	``I just wanted to come out and prove something, that I belong  
on the field,'' Cunningham said. 
</P>
<P>
	San Jose (5-3) tied the game in the 38th minute when defender  
Jamie Clark scored on a pass from Mauricio Wright. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 70th minute, Cunningham scored the winning goal on a  
left-foot shot from 18 yards out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
