<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Showers and occasional thunderstorms stretched from the Rockies  
across the northern Plains on Sunday, with snow falling on some 
mountain ranges. 
</P>
<P>
	A cold front lying across the central Rockies produced showers  
across parts of northern Utah, western Wyoming and Montana. Light 
showers also were scattered over Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	Snow fell at higher elevations of Utah, northern Idaho and  
western Montana, with 2 to 4 inches possible in some areas. 
</P>
<P>
	From Montana, rain stretched eastward across the Dakota into  
northern Minnesota, and a few thunderstorms developed over eastern 
North Dakota and Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	Thunderstorms also were possible over parts of Nebraska, Kansas,  
Oklahoma and Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers and isolated thundershowers moved across Tennessee.  
</P>
<P>
	In the Southeast, thunderstorms built up across southern and  
central Florida during the afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	Elsewhere, scattered showers rolled across upstate New York,  
Vermont, New Hampshire, Massachusetts and Maine. 
</P>
<P>
	Sunday's temperatures around the Lower 48 states ranged from a  
morning low of 19 at Rome, Ore., to an early afternoon reading of 
90 at Houston and Harlingen, Texas. The lowest wind chill was 4 at 
Jerome, Idaho, and the highest heat index by early afternoon was 
102 at McAllen, Texas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
