</P>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stock prices rose in early trading Monday  
amid hopes for fresh measures by the Japanese government to 
stimulate the economy. The Nikkei Stock Average rose 113.89 points 
to 17,060.41 points in the first 30 minutes of trading. 

</P>
