<HEADLINE> Tigers' Palmer Out Indefinitely </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Detroit Tigers third baseman Dean Palmer broke  
his right thumb during today's 5-0 loss to the Baltimore Orioles 
and will be sidelined for an undetermined period. 
</P>
<P>
	Palmer was injured while fielding a hard smash from Baltimore's  
Albert Belle during the third inning. The ball glanced off his 
hand, but he recovered in time and threw out Belle. 
</P>
<P>
	Palmer remained in the game until the fifth, when he was  
replaced by Frank Catalanotto. Palmer was taken to a hospital for 
X-rays, which the club originally said were negative. After the 
game, Detroit announced there was a fracture. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's not much treatment you can do in a situation like  
that,'' Palmer said. ``I don't expect to be out very long.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Palmer joined Detroit this season after signing a $36 million,  
five-year contract as a free agent. He's hitting .273 with five 
homers and 15 RBIs. 
</P>
