<HEADLINE> Mother Charged in Daughter's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- A woman who said she was enraged that her  
8-year-old daughter wet her pants was charged Sunday with beating 
the girl to death with a baseball bat. 
</P>
<P>
	Anita Simmons, 36, told investigators she hit the girl eight or  
nine times on the head and shoulders Saturday morning. Six siblings 
also were home at the time. 
</P>
<P>
	``The mother indicated to the investigators that the child was  
wetting her pants at the age of 8, and that infuriated her,'' said 
Orange County Sheriff's Sgt. Bernard Presha. 
</P>
<P>
	Simmons' boyfriend, Darryl Thomas, 31, called for help when he  
got home shortly before midnight, at least 13 hours later, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl, Causla Nicole Glover, was pronounced dead early  
Sunday, Presha said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Simmons faced a bail hearing Monday on a second-degree  
murder charge. 
</P>
